1. Create a new user:
Request Type: POST
Endpoint: https://gorest.co.in/public-api/users
Request Body:
json
Copy code
{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "johndoe@example.com",
    "gender": "male",
    "status": "active"
}
Expected Response: HTTP status code 201 (Created), and the response body containing the details of the created user, including the user ID.

2. Get user details:
Request Type: GET
Endpoint: https://gorest.co.in/public-api/users/{user_id}
Request Parameters: Replace {user_id} with the ID of the user you want to retrieve.
Expected Response: HTTP status code 200 (OK), and the response body containing the details of the user with the specified user ID.

3. Update user details:
Request Type: PUT
Endpoint: https://gorest.co.in/public-api/users/{user_id}
Request Parameters: Replace {user_id} with the ID of the user you want to update.
Request Body: Provide the updated details for the user.
json
Copy code
{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "johndoe@example.com",
    "gender": "male",
    "status": "inactive"
}
Expected Response: HTTP status code 200 (OK), and the response body containing the updated details of the user.
